'''Crotopo Soup''' ==Ingredients== * [[Cookbook:Clear soup|clear soup]] * 1/2 pound lean [[Cookbook:Veal|veal]] * 3 oz cooked [[Cookbook:Ham|ham]] * 1 [[Cookbook:egg yolk|egg yolk]] * [[Cookbook:Salt|salt]] * [[Cookbook:Pepper|pepper]] * pinch of [[Cookbook:Nutmeg|nutmeg]] * [[Cookbook:Roll|rolls]]
==Procedure== # Pound the veal in a mortar. # Add ham with some fat in it, the egg yolk, salt, pepper, and very little nutmeg, and pound some more. # Pass through a sieve. # Cut some small French rolls into slices and spread them with the above mixture. # Place them in the oven and cook until colored. # Cut the rolls in halves or quarters, and place them in a tureen. # Just before serving, pour a very good clear soup over them.
