'''Steak tartare''' is a meat dish made from finely chopped, or ground raw [[Cookbook:Beef|beef]]. It is often served with [[Cookbook:Onion|onions]] and seasonings, and sometimes with raw [[Cookbook:Egg|egg]].
This dish is popular in [[w:Belgium|Belgium]], where it is known as ''Filet américain'' ("American fillet").
== Ingredients == * 1/2 pound (225g) of quality beef (filet mignon) with all connective tissue removed. * One egg yolk. * One Teaspoon [[w:Worcestershire sauce|Worcestershire]] or [[Cookbook:Soy sauce|Soy]] sauce. * One Tablespoon whole grain [[Cookbook:Mustard|mustard]]. * 1-3 drops of hot pepper sauce, as desired. * 2 Tablespoons of chopped onions. * Salt and fresh ground pepper to taste.
== Procedure == # Finely chop the beef, or run twice through a meat grinder with 1/4 inch (0.75cm) plate. # Mix all the ingredients loosely and spread on bread slices ([[w:Rye|Rye]], [[w: Pumpernickel|Pumpernickel]], etc.) to make open-faced [[Cookbook:Sandwiches|sandwiches]]. The steak tartare may also be served on buttered [[Cookbook:Toast|toast]]. Serve on chilled plates with a favorite beverage.
'''Note that consumption of steak tartare made with contaminated ingredients can cause serious illness or death. It is very likely that one can contract either pathogenic E Coli infection or salmonellosis since even the best ground beef is a composite of many different slaughtered animals, increasing the risk incrementally.'''
{{wikipedia|Steak tartare}}
