To make '''Ham Sauce''' (in [[Italian language|Italian]], '''''Salsa di Prosciutto'''''):
== Ingredients == *[[Cookbook:Ham|ham]] *Musca or sweet [[Cookbook:Port|port]] *[[Cookbook:Vinegar|vinegar]] *[[Cookbook:Basil|basil]] *[[Cookbook:Spice|spice]]
== Procedure == Cut up an ounce (28g)of ham and pound it in a mortar, then mix it with three dessert spoonsful of port or Musca and a teaspoonful of vinegar, a little dried basil and a pinch of spice. Boil it up, and then pass it through a sieve and warm it up in a [[Cookbook:Bain-marie|bain-marie]]. Serve with roast meats. If you cannot get a sweet [[Cookbook:Wine|wine]] add half a teaspoonful of [[Cookbook:Sugar|sugar]]. Australian Muscat is a good wine to use.
