'''Meringue''' is sweetened, whipped [[Cookbook:Egg|egg]] white that has been cooked.  It forms the top of desserts such as [[Cookbook:Lemon Meringue Pie|lemon meringue pie]], in which case it is browned on top but remains soft in the center.  It is also a predominant characteristic of a [[Cookbook:Pavlova|Pavlova]].  Baked at lower heat for a longer time, it dries to form a crunchy confection ([[Cookbook:Meringues|meringues]]), and can be eaten on its own.

