Spaghetti and meatballs for 8
==Ingredients== *1 lb ground beef, 80% lean or better *1 large egg *1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese *1 1/2 cups Italian bread crumbs *2 jars spaghetti sauce *1 lb spaghetti or other pasta *additional Parmesan cheese for serving
== Procedure == # Combine beef, egg, cheese and bread crumbs in bowl and mix thoroughly with hands. # Roll meatball mixture into small balls, about 1/2 to 1 inch diameter. # Fry meatballs in batches over medium heat while turning, until a crust forms on all sides. # Meanwhile, bring one jar of sauce to a simmer in a medium saucepan. # Remove meatballs from frying pan with a slotted spoon to allow them to drain briefly as you transfer them to the pot of sauce. # Simmer meatballs in sauce over low heat for a half hour before starting pasta. # Cook pasta in large pot according to package directions to [[Coobook:al dente|al dente]]] stage. # Pour pasta into colander and rinse with hot water. # Return pasta to pot and add second jar of spaghetti sauce. Bring to a simmer. # To serve, place sauced pasta on plate, top with meatballs in sauce, and sprinkle Parmesan on top if desired.
