{{recipesummary|Turkish recipes|8 pieces|30 minutes + cooling|2|Image=[[Image:Loukoum.jpg|300px|A single piece]]}} {{recipe}}
'''Turkish Delight''', or '''lokum''' (also loukoum), is a confection made from starch and sugar. It is often flavored with rosewater or lemon, the former giving it a characteristic pale pink color. It has a soft, sticky consistency, and is often packaged and eaten in small cubes that are dusted with sugar to prevent sticking. Some recipes include small nut pieces, usually pistachio, hazelnut or walnuts. == Ingredients == * 2 [[Cookbook:cup|cups]] [[Cookbook:sugar|sugar]] * 0.5 [[Cookbook:cup|cups]] [[Cookbook:cornstarch|cornstarch]] * 1.5 [[Cookbook:cup|cups]] water * 0.5 [[Cookbook:teaspoon|tsp]] [[Cookbook:Cream of Tartar|cream of tartar]] * 2 [[Cookbook:tablespoon|tbls]] [[Cookbook:rosewater|rosewater]] or one of the following to taste: ** 0.5 [[Cookbook:teaspoon|tsp]] rose food flavoring ** 0.25 [[Cookbook:cup|cup]] [[Cookbook:fruit juice|fruit juice]] ** 1 [[Cookbook:tablespoon|tbl]] [[Cookbook:Vanilla|vanilla extract]] ** 1 [[Cookbook:tablespoon|tbl]] orange extract ** 1 [[Cookbook:tablespoon|tbl]] [[Cookbook:Crème de menthe|Crème de menthe]] liqueur * Food coloring * 0.5 [[Cookbook:cup|cup]] chopped toasted [[Cookbook:pistachio|pistachios]] or [[Cookbook:almond|almonds]] * [[Cookbook:icing sugar|icing sugar]], granulated sugar, or [[Cookbook:coconut|desiccated coconut]] for dusting
==Procedure== #Combine sugar, 1 cu water, cream of tartar, and flavoring(s) in a small saucepan and bring to a boil. #Boil over medium-low heat for 20-30 minutes, until the mixture reaches "[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Candy#Sugar_stages firm-ball]," or 250°F ''(120°C)'' on a candy thermometer. #In a separate bowl, combine cornstarch with remaining water, mix completely, and slowly stir into sugar mixture. Stir constantly until mixture is evenly combined. #Apply non-stick cooking spray to a form (ice cube trays will do nicely, though not plastic ones), shallow pie pan, or jelly-roll pan. #Pour the hot mixture into the pan or form and allow to set. #When cool, release from form or cut into cubes as applicable and roll each piece in powdered sugar, granulated sugar, or coconut. #Store at room temperature in airtight container.
==Notes, tips and variations== Note: with the exception of the sugar, cornstarch, water, cream of tartar, and cooking technique, this recipe may be greatly altered according to taste and/or occasion. The nuts may be omitted, and various flavorings can be added.
{{wikipedia|Turkish Delight}}
