==Ingredients== * 500 ml. Iraqi [[Cookbook:date|date]]s, chopped and seeded * water * salt * 125 ml. chopped [[Cookbook:walnut|walnut]]s or [[Cookbook:pistachio|pistachio]]s
== Procedure == # Boil dates in lightly salted water stirring frequently until it is a thick paste. # Mix in finely chopped nuts. # A traditional variant is to strain the pulp out of the paste producing a honey-like date syrup. This procedure uses considerably more dates and can take several days to produce sufficient syrup.
